HEADWORD: Paddy
<hw>Pad"dy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Prov. E.
<ets>paddy</ets> worm-eaten.]</ety> <def>Low; mean; boorish;
vagabond.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Such <xex>pady</xex> persons.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Digges
(1585).</au> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>paddy</xex> persons.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Motley.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

